# gitleaks baseline — reviewed historical findings that are NOT live secrets.
#
# gitleaks auto-loads this file (fingerprint = commit:file:rule:startline) from the scan
# root, so both CI's `gitleaks git` job and the local hk `gitleaks` step honour it. It
# suppresses ONLY these exact findings at these exact locations in history; the full default
# ruleset stays active, so any NEW secret still fails the gate.
#
# Each entry below was individually inspected (see the session notes / git blame of this file).
# None are exploitable: they are documentation examples, a bare PEM marker line, or secrets
# that were rotated out long ago (the app moved to Rails credentials / secret_key_base; the
# Errbit host is dead). They live only in git history reaching back to 2012 — rewriting
# history across ~3900 commits to purge dead values isn't worth the disruption.

